Ask HN: Review my dev portfolio startup
text:
Hey, Felix from Stage here

Over the last couple of months we talked to engineers at the biggest tech companies like Google, Uber, Zillow & so many more to gain a good understanding how to approach the portfolio & dev reputation game.

The developer portfolio is a major part in presenting yourself as an developer. So we thought there could be an opportunity to improve this type of work & make it less painful, automate more & provide high value, so, today I'm proud to present you:

https://getstage.app – Stage is an API based developer portfolio, bring your data from sources like GitHub, LinkedIn, Spotify & more, ootb gorgeous design & be always in-sync. You can even create custom extensions w/ code.

With the layoffs crushing our industry atm, it's the first time in like a decade were it's even more important to have a good presentation online if you're affected. With our approach of fetching data from other sources, you don't go to update-hell. Just use the platforms & services you are anyway using.

What will it cost you ask? Creating a portfolio will be free, forever. We currently thinking about adding an paid analytics layer on top of it & also 1 really interested feature which was highly requested –> Tailoring: Fork your portfolio for a specific job or audience. Highlight / Hide different things based on one specific job description for example.

But there is so much more!! We're really exicited to ship an alpha version by the end of the year and would be so happy if you share what you think :)

Ask HN: Does anyone use Terraform to deploy Kubernetes services in a large org?
text: Terraform supports Kubernetes service provisioning, but I've never seen anyone talk about using it at scale. On the surface, I worry a bit that there could be some impedance mismatch or bugginess, due to the layering-on of two state management solutions. Curious how it works in practice.
